📦 Installation
1. Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/data-sentinel.git
cd data-sentinel
2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Configure environment

Create .env file:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/datasentinel
5. Run backend
uvicorn backend.app.main:app --reload
6. Run frontend
streamlit run frontend/dashboard.py
🐳 Docker (Optional)
docker compose up -d
📡 API Endpoints
Endpoint	Description
POST /upload-csv	Upload dataset
GET /reports	Get all reports
GET /reports/{id}	Get single report
GET /reports/{id}/status	AI processing status
📊 Example Output
{
  "rows": 143,
  "columns": 11,
  "missing_values": {},
  "column_health": {},
  "dataset_health_score": 45.45
}
🔐 Design Notes
AI layer is optional and non-blocking
NumPy types normalized before DB insertion
Background tasks handle AI processing
System works fully without OpenAI
📌 Roadmap
 Advanced drift scoring (KL divergence)
 Real-time streaming ingestion
 Authentication system
 Dataset comparison UI
 Scheduled monitoring jobs
